The paper deals with designing auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of online learning techniques, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's focus on revenue guarantees and optimizing auction outcomes falls under the category of computational economics (cs.EC). Finally, the paper's use of duality frameworks and technical conditions suggests a connection to optimization and machine learning (cs.LG).
